    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks for the info around that -- I'd figured there was something generating it, but didn't know where to look. \n\nHonestly though, that maximum width is a pretty large usability issue with what's otherwise a great tool. Any time I set up a new IPython install for myself or introduce someone else to the tool, I'm constantly having to make that adjustment to work around the flaw. Is there some way within the bootstrap framework to generate a percentage-based width rather than a fixed width?\n"
  },
