    "updated_at": "2014-01-22T05:57:39Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think it would be quite difficult to use bootstrap with percentage based widths like this. Also, we are deliberately keeping the width down for the following reasons:\n- At the 1170px width, you are looking at code cells that are over 130 chars wide. This is wider than almost everyone writes code.\n- At the 1170px width, you are looking at ~140 chars of Markdown text. This is _way_ over the recommended 45-90 chars/line considered good typography (http://practicaltypography.com/line-length.html).\n\nBut add the following to your `.ipython/profile_default/static/custom/custom.css`:\n\n``` css\ndiv#notebook > div.container {\n    width: 98%;\n}\n```\n\nTo get the effect you want.\n\nClosing.\n"
  },
