    "updated_at": "2014-01-22T14:51:21Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Good suggestion for the override, thanks.\n\nAlso, just to give some context, this is not so much a problem for the input width as you pointed out, but it is for the output width. A large pandas DataFrame or a large plot is much more difficult to take in when the div width is significantly lower than the monitor's resolution width since you end up with a lot of wasted space on the left side of the centered div. Since most of my work in IPython Notebook tends to involve one or both of those in most cases, it's been a source of irritation.\n"
